{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"nvidiaTeslaT4","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":9595300},{"sourceType":"kernelVersion","sourceId":336283080}],"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"6921b465-7d7d-45d2-adba-c615f7623b51","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# PASS — Progression-Aware Semi-Supervised Learning (complete notebook)\n\n> Full replacement for `gtc-ssl-v5__2_.ipynb`. Runs R0 → R4 + Grassmannian ablation from one config cell.\n> Reassemble the fenced blocks below into a `.ipynb` in order (a ready-made `.ipynb` is provided alongside this file).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Summary of every change relative to the base notebook\n\n**Confusion-flow matrix Φ (new, Cell 10b).** `ConfusionFlowTracker` maintains a K×K matrix initialised to the *literal* identity — `torch.eye(8)`, no AREDS or clinical prior anywhere in the initialisation. Each epoch it fuses two estimators: `C[i][j]`, the teacher's mean softmax probability of class *j* over true-label-*i* samples on the **labeled** set (teacher in eval mode, deterministic eval transform, one extra ~2.4k-image pass ≈ 10 s/epoch), and `T[i][j]`, the fraction of accepted pseudo-labels that were class *i* last epoch and are class *j* this epoch on the **unlabeled** set. The fusion is `Φ̃ = 0.5·C + 0.5·T`, EMA-smoothed with `m=0.9`. T requires stable per-sample identity across epochs, so the unlabeled `Dataset.__getitem__` now returns `(weak, strong, idx)` and the tracker keeps a length-13,872 pseudo-label memory. Φ is updated and logged **every epoch in every run mode**, including R0 — Φ's evolution under plain FixMatch is itself the Figure-1/2 diagnostic.\n\n**Directional debiasing (new, Cell 10b).** `inflow_j(q) = Σ_{i≠j} Φ[i][j]·q_i` implemented as `q @ Φ_offdiag` (the zeroed diagonal is what enforces `i≠j`); `u = (inflow + ε)/Σ(inflow + ε)` with `ε=1e-3`; `z̃ = z − λ_d·ReLU(log(K·u))`. **The ReLU is one-sided and mandatory** — verified in Cell 10e, see §3. At `Φ = I` inflow is identically zero, `u` is uniform, `log(K·(1/K)) = 0`, and the correction is *exactly* zero (not approximately — Cell 10c prints `max|z̃−z| = 0.000e+00`). The mechanism self-warms-up; the 10-epoch linear ramp on `λ_d` is kept anyway as the safety belt the plan asks for.\n\n**Ordinal-entropy acceptance gate (new, Cell 10b).** Neighbourhoods are derived **from Φ itself**, never hand-coded: `Ψ = (Φ+Φᵀ)/2`, diagonal zeroed, `N(j)` = the top-2 entries of row *j* that strictly exceed the mean off-diagonal of Ψ. Classes with no learned confusion get an **empty** `N(j)`. Accept iff `q̃_ĵ ≥ τ_lo = 0.45` **and** `distal_mass ≤ β = 0.10`; accepted samples train on the distribution restricted to `{ĵ} ∪ N(ĵ)` and renormalised (distal mass is *stripped*, not down-weighted). Note the clean degradation: with `N(ĵ) = ∅` the two conditions collapse to a hard threshold at `max(τ_lo, 1−β) = 0.90` and the soft target collapses to a one-hot — i.e. FixMatch. That is the intended fallback and it is what happens at epoch 0 when `Φ = I`.\n\n**Asymmetric under-grading cost (new, Cell 10b).** `w(y,c) = (1+|r_y−r_c|)^γ · (1 + β_u·1[r_c < r_y])` with `γ=1, β_u=0.5`, precomputed as an 8×8 matrix. Ranks: `NORMAL=0, DRUSEN=1, CNV=2`, everything else `−1` → weight 1. Applied as a per-sample multiplier on both `L_sup` and the accepted-pseudo-label loss. `FocalLoss` gained a `reduction` argument so it can return per-sample losses; the default is still `'mean'`, so Cell 13's use of it as an eval criterion is byte-identical to the base notebook.\n\n**Bug 1 — `weak_k` variable lifetime (fixed, Cell 12).** The prior draft called the teacher once for logits, immediately `del weak_k`, then referenced `weak_k` again inside the optional Grassmannian branch — a `NameError` that only fires when `USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE=True`, i.e. it passes every default run and dies on the ablation you'd run last. Fixed by doing **one** teacher forward with `return_tokens=USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE` and caching `M_t_k` *inside the same `torch.no_grad()` block* while `weak_k` is still valid. The single `del weak_k` is placed after that block, after the tensor's last use. This is also strictly cheaper than the two-forward alternative.\n\n**Bug 2 — the two hot inner loops are vectorised (fixed, Cell 10b/12).** Pseudo-label transition counting uses `torch.bincount` on a flattened `i*K + j` index plus `index_put_` for the pseudo-label memory write; the gate's local/distal split uses row-gather + `scatter_` + a masked sum. No Python-level `for` over the batch dimension anywhere in the μ-chunk path (μ=4 chunks × 76 steps × 80 epochs on a T4 — a per-sample loop here is not survivable).\n\n**Bug 3 — device consistency (fixed, Cell 10b).** `idx` arrives from the DataLoader as a CPU `LongTensor` while `prev_pl` / `cur_pl` live on CUDA. `record_chunk` moves it explicitly and asserts the devices match before any indexing.\n\n**Run modes (Cell 0).** Four booleans — `PASS_USE_DEBIAS`, `PASS_USE_GATE`, `PASS_USE_ASYM_COST`, `USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE` — reproduce R0–R4 + the Grassmannian ablation without touching another cell. With `PASS_USE_GATE=False` the loop falls back to the base notebook's hard `TAU=0.95` FixMatch threshold and hard labels, so R0 and R1 are faithful baselines rather than broken variants.\n\n**Preserved exactly:** backbone, EMA update, augmentation pipeline, optimiser/scheduler, AMP, μ-chunking, checkpointing, temperature scaling, 5-pass TTA, evaluation. This is a loss-and-gate patch.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Assumptions made where the spec was underspecified\n\nEach is also stated as a one-line comment at the point of use.\n\n| # | Underspecified | Decision |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `λ_d_max` value | `1.0`. The plan sweeps `{0.3, 0.5, 1.0}`; 1.0 is the value at which the correction actually exceeds a typical boundary logit gap (measured — see §3). Exposed as `PASS_LAMBDA_D_MAX`. |\n| 2 | `T` row with zero accepted transitions | Falls back to the **identity row**. \"No observed drift ⇒ no flow.\" Conservative: pulls Φ toward `I`, never invents structure. |\n| 3 | What `c` is in the per-sample `w(y,c)` | The model's **current decision**: `w_i = W[y_i, argmax_c p_i,c]`, detached. A smooth `mode='expected'` (`Σ_c p_c·W[y,c]`) is also implemented and one flag away. |\n| 4 | Teacher softmax temperature | `1.0`, preserving base-notebook behaviour exactly. Exposed as `PASS_TEACHER_TEMP`. |\n| 5 | Augmentation for the `C` estimator | A dedicated deterministic `labeled_eval_loader` (eval transform, no shuffle), rather than reusing the randomly-augmented training loader. Lower variance, matches \"teacher in eval mode\". |\n\n---\n\n## 3. What I measured (before wiring anything into the training loop)\n\nThese are the actual numbers from the scratch verification, using a Φ **reconstructed from your reported GTC-v5 classification report** (TP/FP/FN back-solved from the per-class precision/recall — the reconstruction reproduces your 0.9156 accuracy exactly, so it is your real confusion structure, not a guess).\n\n**Proposition 1 holds exactly — but only at `ε → 0`.** With `ε=0`, float64, B=512: `max abs error = 8.88e-16`. With the production `ε=1e-3` the same comparison gives `5.1e-3`. So the reduction is exact algebra in the `ε→0` limit, and `ε` is a numerical floor sitting *outside* the algebra. **The verification cell uses `ε=0` for this reason**, and says so. If you claim \"verified to machine precision\" in the paper, that is the claim you can defend.\n\n**The ReLU is mandatory — and the reason is subtler than \"it boosts the easy classes\".** On a torn NORMAL/DRUSEN sample at `λ_d=1.0`:\n\n| | argmax | conf | distal mass |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| raw teacher | NORMAL | 0.524 | 0.0154 |\n| two-sided (no ReLU) | DRUSEN | 0.509 | **0.0431**  (2.8× blow-up) |\n| one-sided (ReLU) | DRUSEN | 0.521 | **0.0217**  (1.4×, contained) |\n\nThe one-sided version flips the argmax to the under-represented class *and* keeps distal mass low. Two things you should know that the plan does not say:\n\n1. **The distal blow-up I reproduce is 2.8×, not the 6× (0.030 → 0.181) in the plan.** The direction and mechanism replicate robustly; the magnitude does not. In my reconstruction the two-sided version's distal mass (0.043) still clears `β=0.10`, so it would *not* have been rejected by the gate. Don't put the 0.030 → 0.181 numbers in the paper without re-deriving them from the *actual* learned Φ at epoch 80. The safe, defensible claim is the ratio: one-sided contains distal inflation to ~1.4× where two-sided is ~2.8×.\n\n2. **The mechanism only fires if Φ is strongly asymmetric on the spectrum.** My first attempt used a near-symmetric Φ (`Φ[D→N]=0.160`, `Φ[N→D]=0.140`) and the argmax did **not** flip and distal mass rose *above* β — the method did nothing. That is not a bug, it is the method's actual precondition: `inflow_NORMAL ≈ Φ[D→N]·q_D` and `inflow_DRUSEN ≈ Φ[N→D]·q_N`, so if `Φ[D→N] ≈ Φ[N→D]` both classes get the same discount and nothing moves. Your data does satisfy this (`Φ[D→N]/Φ[N→D] = 1.68×` in the reconstruction — NORMAL absorbs, DRUSEN donates), which is exactly the precision/recall asymmetry your results table already shows. **But it means the R0 decision gate is sharper than the plan implies: if Φ at epoch 80 comes back roughly symmetric on (N,D), directional debiasing will be a no-op and you should know that before spending R1–R4.** Cell 14b prints this ratio every epoch.\n\n**Neighbourhoods recovered from Φ alone:** `N(NORMAL) = {DME, DRUSEN}`, `N(DRUSEN) = {CNV, NORMAL}`, `N(CNV) = {DME, DRUSEN}`, and `N(AMD) = N(CSR) = ∅`. **CNV ∉ N(NORMAL)** — near-zero (N,C), both confusable with DRUSEN. That is the AREDS chain, recovered without being told it exists.\n\n**Four-case gate test** (`τ_lo=0.45, β=0.10, λ_d=1.0`):\n\n| case | conf | distal | FixMatch (0.95) | PASS |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| (a) boundary NORMAL/DRUSEN *(learned-adjacent)* | 0.521 | 0.0217 | ❌ deleted | ✅ ACCEPT → DRUSEN |\n| (b) confident AMD *(easy, off-spectrum)* | 0.999 | 0.0007 | ✅ | ✅ (‖Δq‖∞ = 2.0e-4 — untouched) |\n| (c) near-uniform garbage | 0.145 | 0.855 | ❌ | ❌ reject |\n| (d) boundary NORMAL/DR *(**not** learned-adjacent)* | 0.537 | 0.463 | ❌ | ❌ **reject** |\n\n(a) vs (d): confidence 0.521 vs 0.537 — **nearly identical**. Distal mass 0.022 vs 0.463 — **21× apart**. A plain lowered threshold accepts both. PASS accepts (a) and rejects (d). That is the figure.\n\n> Sandbox note: this container has no GPU and no network, so torch could not be installed. The verification above was run in NumPy, whose `softmax / matmul / relu / log / topk / bincount` map 1:1 onto the torch ops used in the notebook. Cells 10c–10f re-run all four checks **in torch, on device, at notebook runtime** — they are asserts, not decoration. Run them before you launch R0.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The notebook","metadata":{}},{"id":"ff59b3b5-f548-427f-8676-3fc3be2855c1","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# PASS — Progression-Aware Semi-Supervised Learning for Retinal OCT\n\n> Ordinal collapse in FixMatch-family SSL, and how to undo it with a learned confusion-flow matrix Φ.\n>\n> **One notebook, six runs.** Toggle the flags in Cell 0:\n>\n> | Run | `PASS_USE_DEBIAS` | `PASS_USE_GATE` | `PASS_USE_ASYM_COST` | `USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE` |\n> |---|---|---|---|---|\n> | **R0** instrumented FixMatch baseline | ☐ | ☐ | ☐ | ☐ |\n> | **R1** directional debiasing only | ☑ | ☐ | ☐ | ☐ |\n> | **R2** ordinal gate only | ☐ | ☑ | ☐ | ☐ |\n> | **R3** PASS core | ☑ | ☑ | ☐ | ☐ |\n> | **R4** PASS full | ☑ | ☑ | ☑ | ☐ |\n> | **Grassmannian ablation** | ☑ | ☑ | ☑ | ☑ |\n>\n> Φ is estimated and logged **every epoch in every run mode**, including R0 — Φ's evolution under plain\n> FixMatch *is* the diagnostic (Figures 1 & 2).\n>\n> ### Diagnostic honesty\n> Per-class pseudo-label **purity** (Figure 1, lower panel) is computed against the unlabeled set's\n> held-out ground-truth labels. **These labels are used for diagnostic analysis only. They never enter\n> the loss, the pseudo-label acceptance decision, Φ, the checkpoint criterion, or model selection.**\n> Set `PASS_LOG_PURITY = False` to remove the dependency entirely and confirm the training curve is\n> unchanged. Say this in the figure caption and in the text — reviewers watch for it.","metadata":{}},{"id":"84078db4-91e8-4669-9b0b-a064021b20e2","cell_type":"code","source":"import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nimport torch.nn.functional as F\nfrom torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\nfrom torch.amp import GradScaler, autocast   # new device-aware API\nimport torchvision\nimport torchvision.transforms as T\nimport torchvision.transforms.functional as TF\nfrom PIL import Image\n\nimport gc\nimport psutil\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\nimport os, cv2, math, warnings, time, json, copy\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\nfrom sklearn.metrics import (\n    accuracy_score, classification_report,\n    roc_auc_score, roc_curve, auc,\n    precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\n    confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay,\n)\nfrom tqdm.auto import tqdm\n\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\n\n# ── Reproducibility ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSEED = 15                 # R7/R8 significance seeds: change to 16, 17\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\ntorch.manual_seed(SEED)\ntorch.cuda.manual_seed_all(SEED)\ntorch.backends.cudnn.deterministic = False\ntorch.backends.cudnn.benchmark     = True\n\n# ── TF32 — free ~3× matmul speedup on T4/A100 with no accuracy loss ──────────\ntorch.backends.cuda.matmul.allow_tf32 = True\ntorch.backends.cudnn.allow_tf32       = True\n\nimport torch.multiprocessing\ntorch.multiprocessing.set_sharing_strategy('file_system')\n\n# ── OpenCV thread-pool cap ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# cv2 spawns its own internal thread pool per process by default. With\n# num_workers>0 DataLoader workers each independently decoding images via\n# cv2.imread, that is N worker processes x cv2's own threads all competing for\n# CPU and native (non-Python-heap) memory that gc.collect()/malloc_trim() in\n# the MAIN process can never see or reclaim. Left unset, this was the likely\n# source of the slow, monotonic CPU-memory growth (~1.7-2GB/epoch) that\n# exhausted /dev/shm around epoch 12 even after persistent_workers=True made\n# the DataLoader-iterator-respawn leak go away. One decode thread per worker\n# process is the correct, low-risk setting for this data-loading pattern.\ncv2.setNumThreads(0)\n\nimport ctypes as _ctypes\ntry:\n    _libc = _ctypes.CDLL('libc.so.6')\n    _libc.malloc_trim(0)\n    _MALLOC_TRIM_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept Exception:\n    _MALLOC_TRIM_AVAILABLE = False\nprint(f'malloc_trim available: {_MALLOC_TRIM_AVAILABLE}')\n\nif torch.cuda.is_available():\n    for _i in range(torch.cuda.device_count()):\n        torch.cuda.set_per_process_memory_fraction(0.90, device=_i)\n\n# ── Global config ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nIMG_SIZE    = 224\nBATCH_SIZE  = 32\nNUM_CLASSES = 8\nCLASSES     = sorted(['NORMAL', 'AMD', 'CNV', 'CSR', 'DME', 'DR', 'DRUSEN', 'MH'])\nCLASS2IDX   = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(CLASSES)}\nIDX2CLASS   = {i: c for c, i in CLASS2IDX.items()}\n\nDEVICE      = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\nDEVICE_TYPE = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'\nNUM_GPUS    = torch.cuda.device_count()\nUSE_AMP     = torch.cuda.is_available()\n\n# ── Backbone / SSL hyperparameters (UNCHANGED from base) ─────────────────────\nD_MODEL          = 64\nMU               = 4\nLAMBDA_GRASS_MAX = 1.0\nGRASS_WARMUP     = 16\nLAMBDA_ST        = 0.1\nLAMBDA_DIV       = 0.05\nLAMBDA_PL        = 0.5    # pseudo-label loss weight\nTAU              = 0.95   # FixMatch hard threshold — used when PASS_USE_GATE=False\nEMA_BASE         = 0.996\nRIDGE_EPS        = 1e-6\nEPOCHS           = 80\nLR_MAX           = 3e-4\nLR_MIN           = 1e-7\nWARMUP_EPOCHS    = 8\nPATIENCE         = 12\nMAX_GRAD_NORM    = 1.0\nLABELED_RATIO    = 0.15\n_WORKERS         = 4\n\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n#  ██  PASS CONFIG — the ONLY cell you touch to switch runs  ██\n# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n#\n#   Run                          DEBIAS  GATE  ASYM  GRASS\n#   R0  instrumented FixMatch      ☐      ☐     ☐     ☐\n#   R1  debias only                ☑      ☐     ☐     ☐\n#   R2  gate only                  ☐      ☑     ☐     ☐\n#   R3  PASS core                  ☑      ☑     ☐     ☐\n#   R4  PASS full                  ☑      ☑     ☑     ☐\n#   G   Grassmannian ablation      ☑      ☑     ☑     ☑\n#\nRUN_NAME                = 'R0'      # free-text tag; goes into all output filenames\n\nPASS_USE_DEBIAS         = False     # directional debiasing of teacher logits\nPASS_USE_GATE           = False     # ordinal-entropy gate + neighbourhood soft target\nPASS_USE_ASYM_COST      = False     # asymmetric under-grading cost\nUSE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE = False     # optional geometric second opinion (§7 of the plan)\n\n# ── Φ — confusion-flow matrix ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nPASS_PHI_ALPHA    = 0.5    # Φ̃ = α·C + (1−α)·T.  Raise toward 1.0 if Φ is noisy\n                           # (C is the lower-variance estimator) — plan §5, week 1.\nPASS_PHI_MOMENTUM = 0.9    # Φ ← m·Φ_prev + (1−m)·Φ̃.  Lengthen to 0.95 if noisy.\nPASS_PHI_TOPK     = 2      # |N(j)| ≤ 2\n\n# ── Directional debiasing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ASSUMPTION: λ_d_max is not given in the spec. The plan sweeps {0.3, 0.5, 1.0};\n# 1.0 is the value at which the correction actually exceeds a typical boundary\n# logit gap (measured on a reconstructed Φ — below 1.0 the argmax does not flip).\nPASS_LAMBDA_D_MAX     = 1.0\nPASS_LAMBDA_D_WARMUP  = 10     # linear ramp over the first 10 epochs (safety belt;\n                               # the mechanism already self-warms-up at Φ=I).\nPASS_EPS              = 1e-3   # inflow floor. NOTE: Proposition 1 is exact only as\n                               # ε→0; the Prop-1 verification cell uses ε=0.\nPASS_ONE_SIDED        = True   # ← the ReLU. DO NOT SET FALSE. See Cell 10e.\nPASS_TEACHER_TEMP     = 1.0    # ASSUMPTION: unspecified; 1.0 preserves base behaviour.\n\n# ── Ordinal-entropy acceptance gate ──────────────────────────────────────────\nPASS_TAU_LO = 0.45   # NOT a typo and NOT to be raised. A genuine ordinal boundary\n                     # sample has conf ≈ 0.55 *by definition of being a boundary\n                     # case*. Confidence is not the discriminating signal here —\n                     # distal mass is. τ_lo only rejects near-uniform garbage.\nPASS_BETA   = 0.10   # distal-mass ceiling. THIS is the criterion doing the work.\n\n# ── Asymmetric under-grading cost ────────────────────────────────────────────\nPASS_GAMMA      = 1.0\nPASS_BETA_U     = 0.5        # β_u = 0 recovers a symmetric ordinal cost (ablation)\nPASS_ASYM_MODE  = 'argmax'   # 'argmax' (per-sample, hard, detached) | 'expected' (smooth)\n\n# ── Diagnostics ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Per-class pseudo-label PURITY needs the unlabeled set's held-out labels.\n# DIAGNOSTIC ONLY — never used for training, acceptance, Φ, or model selection.\nPASS_LOG_PURITY = True\n\n# ── Resume & memory mode ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nRESUME_CKPT      = '/kaggle/input/notebooks/ashrafulhossenakash/pass-ssl-v2/pass_R0_periodic_ep035.pt'    # set to a checkpoint path to resume\nCACHE_DATASETS   = False\nUNLABELED_ONDISK = True\n\n_CUDA_CACHE_CLEAR_EVERY = 10\n_GC_COLLECT_EVERY       = 20\n_EPOCH_TIME_WARN_SEC    = 900\n\n\ndef log_mem(tag=''):\n    \"\"\"Print CPU RAM + per-GPU VRAM.\"\"\"\n    cpu_u = psutil.virtual_memory().used      / 1e9\n    cpu_a = psutil.virtual_memory().available / 1e9\n    gpu_s = []\n    for _gi in range(torch.cuda.device_count()):\n        alloc    = torch.cuda.memory_allocated(_gi) / 1e9\n        reserved = torch.cuda.memory_reserved(_gi)  / 1e9\n        gpu_s.append(f'GPU{_gi}: {alloc:.1f}/{reserved:.1f}GB')\n    print(f'  [{tag}] CPU {cpu_u:.1f}GB used / {cpu_a:.1f}GB avail | '\n          + ' | '.join(gpu_s), flush=True)\n\n\nprint(f'Classes (alphabetical): {CLASSES}')\nprint(f'Device  : {DEVICE}  |  GPUs: {NUM_GPUS}  |  AMP: {USE_AMP}')\nprint('=' * 78)\nprint(f'  RUN = {RUN_NAME}   seed={SEED}')\nprint(f'  debias={PASS_USE_DEBIAS}  gate={PASS_USE_GATE}  '\n      f'asym={PASS_USE_ASYM_COST}  grassmannian={USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE}')\nif PASS_USE_GATE:\n    print(f'  gate     : tau_lo={PASS_TAU_LO}  beta={PASS_BETA}')\nelse:\n    print(f'  gate     : OFF -> hard FixMatch threshold TAU={TAU} (faithful baseline)')\nif PASS_USE_DEBIAS:\n    print(f'  debias   : lambda_d_max={PASS_LAMBDA_D_MAX}  ramp={PASS_LAMBDA_D_WARMUP}ep  '\n          f'eps={PASS_EPS}  one_sided={PASS_ONE_SIDED}')\nprint(f'  Phi      : alpha={PASS_PHI_ALPHA}  m={PASS_PHI_MOMENTUM}  '\n      f'topk={PASS_PHI_TOPK}  (logged every epoch in ALL runs)')\nprint('=' * 78)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:41:56.455691Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:41:56.456365Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.570986Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:41:56.45634Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.570309Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"malloc_trim available: True\nClasses (alphabetical): ['AMD', 'CNV', 'CSR', 'DME', 'DR', 'DRUSEN', 'MH', 'NORMAL']\nDevice  : cuda  |  GPUs: 2  |  AMP: True\n==============================================================================\n  RUN = R0   seed=15\n  debias=False  gate=False  asym=False  grassmannian=False\n  gate     : OFF -> hard FixMatch threshold TAU=0.95 (faithful baseline)\n  Phi      : alpha=0.5  m=0.9  topk=2  (logged every epoch in ALL runs)\n==============================================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":1},{"id":"180944ab-7864-43a6-b0fd-458d552bb0bb","cell_type":"code","source":"def enhance_image_np(img_rgb_uint8: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"CLAHE + Unsharp mask — identical to the supervised baseline.\"\"\"\n    lab      = cv2.cvtColor(img_rgb_uint8, cv2.COLOR_RGB2LAB)\n    l, a, b  = cv2.split(lab)\n    clahe    = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=2.0, tileGridSize=(8, 8))\n    l        = clahe.apply(l)\n    enhanced = cv2.cvtColor(cv2.merge([l, a, b]), cv2.COLOR_LAB2RGB)\n    gaussian = cv2.GaussianBlur(enhanced, (5, 5), 1.0)\n    return cv2.addWeighted(enhanced, 1.5, gaussian, -0.5, 0).astype(np.uint8)\n\n\ndef precompute_enhanced(df, img_size=224):\n    \"\"\"Run CLAHE+unsharp once per image, cache as uint8 numpy array.\"\"\"\n    from joblib import Parallel, delayed\n\n    def load_one(path):\n        img = cv2.imread(path)\n        img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n        img = cv2.resize(img, (img_size, img_size))\n        return enhance_image_np(img)\n\n    print(f'  Pre-computing CLAHE for {len(df):,} images ...', end=' ')\n    t0 = time.time()\n    images = Parallel(n_jobs=2)(\n        delayed(load_one)(p) for p in df['filepaths'].tolist()\n    )\n    print(f'done in {time.time()-t0:.1f}s')\n    return np.stack(images, axis=0)\n\n\nprint('Enhancement utilities defined.')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.572377Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.572841Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.581138Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.572814Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.580242Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Enhancement utilities defined.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":2},{"id":"c44e59f7-2b7f-4347-9037-2c208b290312","cell_type":"code","source":"class SEBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, channels, ratio=8):\n        super().__init__()\n        mid = max(1, channels // ratio)\n        self.pool = nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d(1)\n        self.fc   = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Flatten(),\n            nn.Linear(channels, mid), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Linear(mid, channels), nn.Sigmoid()\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        s = self.fc(self.pool(x))\n        return x * s.view(x.size(0), -1, 1, 1)\n\n\nclass CBAMBlock(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Channel + Spatial Attention Module.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, channels, ratio=8, return_attn=False):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.return_attn = return_attn\n        mid = max(1, channels // ratio)\n        self.ch_fc1  = nn.Linear(channels, mid)\n        self.ch_fc2  = nn.Linear(mid, channels)\n        self.sp_conv = nn.Conv2d(2, 1, kernel_size=7, padding=3, bias=False)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        B, C, H, W = x.shape\n        avg_c = x.mean(dim=[2, 3])\n        max_c = x.amax(dim=[2, 3])\n        ch = torch.sigmoid(\n            self.ch_fc2(F.relu(self.ch_fc1(avg_c))) +\n            self.ch_fc2(F.relu(self.ch_fc1(max_c)))\n        ).view(B, C, 1, 1)\n        x = x * ch\n        avg_s = x.mean(dim=1, keepdim=True)\n        max_s = x.amax(dim=1, keepdim=True)\n        sp    = torch.sigmoid(self.sp_conv(torch.cat([avg_s, max_s], dim=1)))\n        out   = x * sp\n        if self.return_attn:\n            return out, sp\n        return out\n\n\nclass IdentityBlock(nn.Module):\n    def __init__(self, channels):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(channels, channels, 3, padding=1, bias=False)\n        self.bn1   = nn.BatchNorm2d(channels)\n        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(channels, channels, 3, padding=1, bias=False)\n        self.bn2   = nn.BatchNorm2d(channels)\n        self.se    = SEBlock(channels)\n        self.relu  = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        out = self.relu(self.bn1(self.conv1(x)))\n        out = self.bn2(self.conv2(out))\n        out = self.se(out)\n        return self.relu(out + x)\n\n\nclass ConvBlock(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Downsampling residual block (stride=2).\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, in_ch, out_ch):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(in_ch, out_ch, 3, stride=2, padding=1, bias=False)\n        self.bn1   = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch)\n        self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(out_ch, out_ch, 3, padding=1, bias=False)\n        self.bn2   = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch)\n        self.se    = SEBlock(out_ch)\n        self.skip  = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Conv2d(in_ch, out_ch, 1, stride=2, bias=False),\n            nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch)\n        )\n        self.relu  = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        out = self.relu(self.bn1(self.conv1(x)))\n        out = self.bn2(self.conv2(out))\n        out = self.se(out)\n        return self.relu(out + self.skip(x))\n\nprint('Architecture blocks defined.')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.582117Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.582425Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.603973Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.582389Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.603063Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Architecture blocks defined.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"9dd30ce5-771a-45e3-a923-31e236d2477e","cell_type":"code","source":"class SinusoidalPositionalEncoding(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Fixed sinusoidal PE — pre-computed at init.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, max_len: int = 3, d_model: int = 64):\n        super().__init__()\n        pe = torch.zeros(max_len, d_model)\n        for pos in range(max_len):\n            for i in range(0, d_model, 2):\n                angle = pos / (10000.0 ** (2 * i / d_model))\n                pe[pos, i] = math.sin(angle)\n                if i + 1 < d_model:\n                    pe[pos, i + 1] = math.cos(angle)\n        self.register_buffer('pe', pe.unsqueeze(0))\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        return x + self.pe[:, :x.size(1)]\n\n\nclass TransformerEncoderBlock(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"Pre-LN Transformer Encoder — d_model=64, num_heads=2, dropout=0.2.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, d_model=64, num_heads=2, dropout_rate=0.2):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.ln1  = nn.LayerNorm(d_model, eps=1e-6)\n        self.mhsa = nn.MultiheadAttention(\n            embed_dim=d_model, num_heads=num_heads,\n            dropout=dropout_rate, batch_first=True\n        )\n        self.drop1 = nn.Dropout(dropout_rate)\n        self.ln2   = nn.LayerNorm(d_model, eps=1e-6)\n        self.ffn   = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(d_model, 4 * d_model), nn.GELU(),\n            nn.Dropout(dropout_rate),\n            nn.Linear(4 * d_model, d_model),\n            nn.Dropout(dropout_rate),\n        )\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        x_ln = self.ln1(x)\n        attn_out, _ = self.mhsa(x_ln, x_ln, x_ln)\n        x = x + self.drop1(attn_out)\n        x = x + self.ffn(self.ln2(x))\n        return x\n\n\nclass TransformerHead(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"PE → TransformerBlock → mean+max aggregate.\"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, d_model=64, num_heads=2, dropout_rate=0.2):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.pe          = SinusoidalPositionalEncoding(max_len=3, d_model=d_model)\n        self.transformer = TransformerEncoderBlock(d_model, num_heads, dropout_rate)\n\n    def forward(self, x):\n        x = self.pe(x)\n        x = self.transformer(x)\n        return x.mean(dim=1) + x.max(dim=1).values\n\nprint('Transformer head defined (d_model=64, num_heads=2).')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.605143Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.605463Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.621769Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.605434Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.620982Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Transformer head defined (d_model=64, num_heads=2).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"f99eba50-2830-4a76-9fc2-f3576ef09cc3","cell_type":"code","source":"class MSCBAMTransformerN1_GTC(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"\n    MS-CBAM-Transformer v2 — GTC variant with token extraction hook.\n    Three branches → (B, 3, 64) token matrix → Transformer → classifier.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, num_classes=8, d_model=64, dropout_cls=(0.4, 0.3)):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.stem = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Conv2d(3, 32, 7, stride=2, padding=3, bias=False),\n            nn.BatchNorm2d(32), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.MaxPool2d(3, stride=2, padding=1)\n        )\n        self.A_res1  = nn.Sequential(ConvBlock(32, 32), IdentityBlock(32), IdentityBlock(32))\n        self.A_cbam1 = CBAMBlock(32)\n        self.A_res2  = nn.Sequential(ConvBlock(32, 64), IdentityBlock(64), IdentityBlock(64))\n        self.A_cbam2 = CBAMBlock(64)\n        self.A_res3  = nn.Sequential(ConvBlock(64, 128), IdentityBlock(128))\n        self.A_cbam3 = CBAMBlock(128, ratio=16, return_attn=True)\n        self.A_proj  = nn.Linear(128, d_model)\n\n        self.B_res1  = nn.Sequential(ConvBlock(32, 32), IdentityBlock(32))\n        self.B_cbam1 = CBAMBlock(32)\n        self.B_res2  = nn.Sequential(ConvBlock(32, 64), IdentityBlock(64))\n        self.B_cbam2 = CBAMBlock(64)\n        self.B_pool  = nn.MaxPool2d(3, padding=1)\n        self.B_proj  = nn.Linear(64, d_model)\n\n        self.C_pool2 = nn.AvgPool2d(2, stride=2)\n        self.C_conv2 = nn.Conv2d(32, 32, 1)\n        self.C_pool4 = nn.AvgPool2d(4, stride=4)\n        self.C_conv4 = nn.Conv2d(32, 32, 1)\n        self.C_proj  = nn.Linear(64, d_model)\n\n        self.transformer = TransformerHead(d_model=d_model, num_heads=2, dropout_rate=0.2)\n\n        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(\n            nn.Linear(d_model, 128), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.BatchNorm1d(128), nn.Dropout(dropout_cls[0]),\n            nn.Linear(128, 64), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n            nn.Dropout(dropout_cls[1]),\n            nn.Linear(64, num_classes)\n        )\n        self._init_weights()\n\n    def _init_weights(self):\n        for m in self.modules():\n            if isinstance(m, nn.Conv2d):\n                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, mode='fan_out', nonlinearity='relu')\n            elif isinstance(m, nn.BatchNorm2d):\n                nn.init.constant_(m.weight, 1)\n                nn.init.constant_(m.bias, 0)\n            elif isinstance(m, nn.Linear):\n                nn.init.xavier_uniform_(m.weight)\n                if m.bias is not None:\n                    nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)\n\n    def _pool_add(self, feat_map):\n        return feat_map.mean(dim=[2, 3]) + feat_map.amax(dim=[2, 3])\n\n    def forward(self, x, return_tokens=False):\n        stem = self.stem(x)\n\n        A = self.A_cbam1(self.A_res1(stem))\n        A = self.A_cbam2(self.A_res2(A))\n        A, _ = self.A_cbam3(self.A_res3(A))\n        A_feat = F.relu(self.A_proj(self._pool_add(A)))\n\n        B = self.B_cbam1(self.B_res1(stem))\n        B = self.B_cbam2(self.B_res2(B))\n        B = self.B_pool(B)\n        B_feat = F.relu(self.B_proj(self._pool_add(B)))\n\n        C2 = F.relu(self.C_conv2(self.C_pool2(stem))).mean(dim=[2, 3])\n        C4 = F.relu(self.C_conv4(self.C_pool4(stem))).mean(dim=[2, 3])\n        C_feat = F.relu(self.C_proj(torch.cat([C2, C4], dim=1)))\n\n        tokens = torch.stack([A_feat, B_feat, C_feat], dim=1)   # (B, 3, 64)\n        agg    = self.transformer(tokens)\n        logits = self.classifier(agg)\n\n        if return_tokens:\n            return logits, tokens\n        return logits\n\nprint('MSCBAMTransformerN1_GTC defined (with token extraction hook).')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.62285Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.623544Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.638887Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.623516Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.63815Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"MSCBAMTransformerN1_GTC defined (with token extraction hook).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"id":"96ed1f2d-0e8b-4f51-b844-1c6814049b6b","cell_type":"code","source":"class FocalLoss(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"\n    Focal Loss with per-class weights and label smoothing.  γ=2.0, ε=0.1.\n\n    PASS CHANGE: added `reduction`. Default 'mean' → byte-identical to the base\n    notebook (Cell 13 uses this as the eval criterion). reduction='none' returns\n    the (B,) per-sample vector, which is what the asymmetric under-grading cost\n    multiplies into.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, gamma=2.0, label_smoothing=0.1, weight=None):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.gamma           = gamma\n        self.label_smoothing = label_smoothing\n        self.weight          = weight\n\n    def forward(self, logits, targets, reduction='mean'):\n        B, C  = logits.shape\n        probs = F.softmax(logits, dim=-1).clamp(1e-8, 1 - 1e-8)\n\n        with torch.no_grad():\n            y_smooth = torch.full_like(probs, self.label_smoothing / C)\n            y_smooth.scatter_(\n                1, targets.unsqueeze(1),\n                1.0 - self.label_smoothing + self.label_smoothing / C\n            )\n\n        ce           = -y_smooth * torch.log(probs)\n        focal_weight = (1.0 - probs) ** self.gamma\n\n        if self.weight is not None:\n            loss_per_sample = (self.weight * focal_weight * ce).sum(dim=-1)\n        else:\n            loss_per_sample = (focal_weight * ce).sum(dim=-1)\n\n        if reduction == 'none':\n            return loss_per_sample            # (B,)\n        return loss_per_sample.mean()         # scalar — base behaviour\n\n\n_CW_MAP = {\n    'DRUSEN': 1.8, 'MH': 1.8, 'DME': 1.6, 'CNV': 1.3,\n    'DR': 1.2, 'NORMAL': 1.5, 'AMD': 1.0, 'CSR': 1.0,\n}\n_CW_LIST = [_CW_MAP.get(c, 1.0) for c in CLASSES]\nCLASS_WEIGHTS_T = torch.tensor(_CW_LIST, dtype=torch.float32, device=DEVICE)\n\nprint(f'Class weights: { {CLASSES[i]: _CW_LIST[i] for i in range(NUM_CLASSES)} }')\nprint('Focal loss defined (with reduction=none support for the asymmetric cost).')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.641057Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.641701Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.928837Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.641679Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.928218Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Class weights: {'AMD': 1.0, 'CNV': 1.3, 'CSR': 1.0, 'DME': 1.6, 'DR': 1.2, 'DRUSEN': 1.8, 'MH': 1.8, 'NORMAL': 1.5}\nFocal loss defined (with reduction=none support for the asymmetric cost).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"b22584ab-44f2-4479-9102-cac4a6a3e500","cell_type":"code","source":"class GrassmannianTokenConsistencyLoss(nn.Module):\n    \"\"\"\n    Optional geometric second opinion (plan §7 — DEMOTED to an ablatable module).\n    Enabled only when USE_GRASSMANNIAN_MODULE=True.\n    \"\"\"\n    def __init__(self, ridge_eps=1e-6):\n        super().__init__()\n        self.ridge_eps = ridge_eps\n\n    def _ridge_qr(self, M):\n        B, k, d = M.shape\n        Mt = M.transpose(1, 2).contiguous()\n        ridge = self.ridge_eps * torch.eye(d, k, device=M.device, dtype=M.dtype).unsqueeze(0)\n        Mt_ridged = Mt + ridge\n        orig_dtype = Mt_ridged.dtype\n        if orig_dtype == torch.float16:          # torch.linalg.qr has no fp16 CUDA kernel\n            Mt_ridged = Mt_ridged.float()\n        Q, R = torch.linalg.qr(Mt_ridged, mode='reduced')\n        return Q.to(orig_dtype)\n\n    def chordal_distance(self, M_s, M_t):\n        B, k, d = M_s.shape\n        Q_s = self._ridge_qr(M_s)\n        Q_t = self._ridge_qr(M_t)\n        B_mat = torch.bmm(Q_s.transpose(1, 2), Q_t)\n        B_frob_sq = (B_mat ** 2).sum(dim=(1, 2))\n        dist_sq = (2.0 * (float(k) - B_frob_sq)).clamp(min=0.0)\n        return dist_sq.mean()\n\n    def stiefel_regularizer(self, M_s):\n        B, k, d = M_s.shape\n        M_hat = M_s / (M_s.norm(dim=(1, 2), keepdim=True) + 1e-8)\n        gram  = torch.bmm(M_hat, M_hat.transpose(1, 2))\n        target = torch.eye(k, device=M_s.device, dtype=M_s.dtype).unsqueeze(0) / float(k)\n        return ((gram - target) ** 2).sum(dim=(1, 2)).mean()\n\n    def token_diversity(self, M_s):\n        M_normed = F.normalize(M_s, p=2, dim=2)\n        cos_sim  = torch.bmm(M_normed, M_normed.transpose(1, 2))\n        loss = (cos_sim[:, 0, 1] ** 2 + cos_sim[:, 0, 2] ** 2 + cos_sim[:, 1, 2] ** 2) / 3.0\n        return loss.mean()\n\n    def forward(self, M_s, M_t):\n        return (self.chordal_distance(M_s, M_t),\n                self.stiefel_regularizer(M_s),\n                self.token_diversity(M_s))\n\nprint('GrassmannianTokenConsistencyLoss defined (optional ablatable module).')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.929835Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.930242Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.94158Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.930219Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-18T16:42:07.941004Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"GrassmannianTokenConsistencyLoss defined (optional ablatable module).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"1f1c7202-d4dd-4743-89bd-1fec3b6cc983","cell_type":"code","source":"@torch.no_grad()\ndef ema_update(student, teacher, alpha):\n    \"\"\"θ_t ← α·θ_t + (1−α)·θ_s. Handles nn.DataParallel transparently. UNCHANGED.\"\"\"\n    student_model = student.